cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complementation of Buchi automata, which is a topic in formal language theory and automata theory, both of which are closely related to logic. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also a likely category as the paper deals with Buchi automata and their complementation constructions. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper proposes optimization heuristics for Buchi complementation constructions, which can be seen as a programming language-related task. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses the performance of different Buchi complementation constructions and proposes optimization heuristics, which are related to algorithmic and data structure-related tasks. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with formal language theory and automata theory, which are both branches of discrete mathematics.
